<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Except for the PTO gears, the left and right countershaft assemblies are identical and
                    disassembled in the same manner.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear retaining snap ring from the front of each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302195">Figure 95</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302195" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302195" filename="../figg13/G1302195.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of the 4th speed gear as a base and press the drive gear, PTO gear, and
                4th speed gear from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302196">Figure 96</hotlnk>). This removes the front bearing inner race from the
                countershafts of models so equipped.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302196" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302196" filename="../figg13/G1302196.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Remove Front Bearing Inner Race</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>NEVER USE THE PTO GEAR AS A PRESSING BASE. The narrow face width of this gear makes it very
                        susceptible to breakage.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of 2nd speed gear as a base and press the 3rd speed and 2nd speed gears
                from each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302197">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302197" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302197" filename="../figg13/G1302197.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 97. 3rd &#38; 2nd Speed Gears</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Always use caution when pressing a cluster of gears from the countershaft. It is necessary to
                        press these gears off in a cluster of three and then, in a cluster of two.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the key and roll pin from the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302198">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302198" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302198" filename="../figg13/G1302198.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Key &#38; Roll Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
